A Papilio demoleus is a species of butterfly commonly known as the Common Lime butterfly.
This butterfly is characterized by its bright yellow and black striped wings with a black spot on each wing.
The wingspan of the Papilio demoleus can range from 7 to 10 cm.
The upper sides of the wings have a smooth texture, while the undersides are more textured.
The body of this butterfly is thin and elongated with six long, slender legs.
The Papilio demoleus can be found in tropical and subtropical regions across Asia, Africa, and Australia.
It is a common sight in gardens, parks and forests, and is known for its graceful flying patterns and stunning beauty.
